This portfolio explores long-term climate patterns in Ukraine over the period 1995â2024, focusing on changes in temperature and precipitation.

Context & Question

How have extreme temperatures changed along with average temperature trends?

Design Decisions

  • I used a combination of a line graph (trends), a heat map (seasonality), and a bar chart/range diagram (minimums-maximums).
  • The color scale from blue to orange intuitively conveys the intensity of cold and heat, while dark blue for the extremes of recent years emphasizes their abnormality. As the season changes, the color of the line also changes.

ð Key Insights

  • There is a clear upward trend in average temperatures, with recent years showing significantly higher extremes.
  • Seasonal patterns are evident, with summers becoming hotter and winters milder.
  • The frequency of extreme temperature events has increased, indicating a shift in climate patterns.

Context & Question

Has total annual precipitation in Ukraine changed over the years?

Design Decisions

  • I chose a line graph to effectively illustrate trends over time.
  • The X-axis is the time scale, the Y-axis is the average precipitation in mm. Annotations for peak values are used.

ð Key Insights

  • The wettest year was 1997 (2.11 mm on average), and the driest was 2014 (1.25 mm).
  • Recent years (2022â2024) show some stabilization of precipitation at above-average levels after a long period of fluctuations.

ð 3 Vizualization: Temperature vs Precipitation: 1995 vs 2024

Context & Question

How has the relationship between temperature and precipitation changed over time?

Design Decisions

  • I used a scatter plot with a breakdown into two time periods.
  • It would be possible to plot the points for both years on a single graph, but separating them makes the comparison clearer and less cluttered.
  • Position encodes temperature and precipitation, while color distinguishes seasons.

ð Key Insights

  • In 2024, summer season points shifted to the right (higher temperatures) compared to 1995.
  • There has been an increase in extremely hot summer days with temperatures above 24 degrees, which did not occur in 1995.
  • Global warming does not cause the same changes in precipitation throughout all seasons.

âï¸ 4 Vizualization: Rainfall and Snowfall Trends in Ukraine

Context & Question

How have rainfall and snowfall patterns changed over the years in Ukraine?

Design Decisions

  • I used a dual-axis line chart to compare rainfall and snowfall trends over time.
  • Two different colors are used to distinguish between rain (green-blue) and snow (blue).
  • Separating graphs helps avoid confusion due to different scales.

ð Key Insights

  • The amount of snow shows a dramatic decline in certain years (for example, critical lows around 2014 and 2020).
  • The rainfall pattern is more stable, although it also has cyclical fluctuations.
  • Snow cover is becoming less permanent and is being replaced by rainfall.

Context & Question

How has the average temperature in Ukraine changed across decades?

Design Decisions

  • I used a bar chart to represent average temperatures for each decade.

  • But you can also look at trends by season separately.

ð Key Insights
